	extbf{First solution:}
The answer is $17/21$. For fixed $sidetwo,sidethr$, there is a triangle of side lengths $sideone,sidetwo,sidethr$ if and only if $|sidetwo-sidethr|<sideone<sidetwo+sidethr$. It follows that the desired sum is
\[
totalsum = \sum_{sidetwo,sidethr}  rac{1}{3^{sidetwo}5^{sidethr}} \left(\sum_{sideone=|sidetwo-sidethr|+1}^{sidetwo+sidethr-1} 2^{sideone} ight) = \sum_{sidetwo,sidethr}  rac{2^{sidetwo+sidethr}-2^{|sidetwo-sidethr|+1}}{3^{sidetwo}5^{sidethr}}.
\]
We write this as $totalsum = totalsum_1+totalsum_2$ where $totalsum_1$ sums over positive integers $sidetwo,sidethr$ with $sidetwo\leq sidethr$ and $totalsum_2$ sums over $sidetwo>sidethr$. Then
 egin{align*}
totalsum_1 &= \sum_{sidetwo=1}^{\infty} \sum_{sidethr=sidetwo}^{\infty}  rac{2^{sidetwo+sidethr}-2^{sidethr-sidetwo+1}}{3^{sidetwo} 5^{sidethr}} \&= \sum_{sidetwo=1}^{\infty} \left( \left( \left( rac{2}{3}ight)^{sidetwo}- rac{2}{6^{sidetwo}} ight) \sum_{sidethr=sidetwo}^{\infty} \left( rac{2}{5} ight)^{sidethr} ight) \&= \sum_{sidetwo=1}^{\infty} \left( \left( rac{2}{3}ight)^{sidetwo}- rac{2}{6^{sidetwo}} ight)  rac{5}{3} \left(  rac{2}{5} ight)^{sidetwo} \&= \sum_{sidetwo=1}^{\infty} \left(  rac{5}{3} \left( rac{4}{15}ight)^{sidetwo} -  rac{10}{3} \left( rac{1}{15}ight)^{sidetwo} ight) \&=  rac{85}{231}.
\end{align*}
Similarly,
 egin{align*}
totalsum_2 &= \sum_{sidethr=1}^{\infty} \sum_{sidetwo=sidethr+1}^{\infty}  rac{2^{sidetwo+sidethr}-2^{sidetwo-sidethr+1}}{3^{sidetwo} 5^{sidethr}} \&= \sum_{sidethr=1}^{\infty} \left( \left( \left( rac{2}{5}ight)^{sidethr}- rac{2}{10^{sidethr}} ight) \sum_{sidetwo=sidethr+1}^{\infty} \left( rac{2}{3} ight)^{sidetwo} ight) \&= \sum_{sidethr=1}^{\infty} \left( \left( rac{2}{5}ight)^{sidethr}- rac{2}{10^{sidethr}} ight) 3 \left(  rac{2}{3} ight)^{sidethr+1} \&= \sum_{sidethr=1}^{\infty} \left( 2 \left( rac{4}{15}ight)^{sidethr} - 4 \left( rac{1}{15}ight)^{sidethr} ight) \&=  rac{34}{77}.
\end{align*}
We conclude that $totalsum = totalsum_1+totalsum_2 =  rac{17}{21}$.


oindent	extbf{Second solution:}
Recall that the real numbers $sideone,sidetwo,sidethr$ form the side lengths of a triangle if and only if
\[
semiper-sideone,\; semiper-sidetwo,\; semiper-sidethr > 0 \qquad semiper =  rac{sideone+sidetwo+sidethr}{2},
\]
and that if we put $auxvarx = 2(semiper-sideone),\; auxvary = 2(semiper-sidetwo),\; auxvarz = 2(semiper-sidethr)$,
\[
sideone =  rac{auxvary+auxvarz}{2}, \quad sidetwo =  rac{auxvarz+auxvarx}{2}, \quad sidethr =  rac{auxvarx+auxvary}{2}.
\]
To generate all \emph{integer} triples $(sideone,sidetwo,sidethr)$ which form the side lengths of a triangle, we must also assume that $auxvarx,auxvary,auxvarz$ are either all even or all odd. We may therefore write the original sum as
\[
%\sum_{(sideone,sidetwo,sidethr) \in tripleset}  rac{2^{sideone}}{3^{sidetwo} 5^{sidethr}}
%=
\sum_{auxvarx,auxvary,auxvarz >0 \mbox{\small \,odd}}  rac{2^{(auxvary+auxvarz)/2}}{3^{(auxvarz+auxvarx)/2} 5^{(auxvarx+auxvary)/2}}
+ \sum_{auxvarx,auxvary,auxvarz >0 \mbox{\small \,even}}  rac{2^{(auxvary+auxvarz)/2}}{3^{(auxvarz+auxvarx)/2} 5^{(auxvarx+auxvary)/2}}.
\]
To unify the two sums, we substitute in the first case  $auxvarx = 2indexuu+1,\; auxvary = 2indexvv+1,\; auxvarz = 2indexww+1$ and in the second case $auxvarx = 2indexuu+2,\; auxvary = 2indexvv+2,\; auxvarz = 2indexww+2$ to obtain
 egin{align*}
\sum_{(sideone,sidetwo,sidethr) \in tripleset}  rac{2^{sideone}}{3^{sidetwo} 5^{sidethr}}
&= \sum_{indexuu,indexvv,indexww=1}^{\infty}  rac{2^{indexvv+indexww}}{3^{indexww+indexuu} 5^{indexuu+indexvv}} \left( 1 +  rac{2^{-1}}{3^{-1} 5^{-1}} ight) \&=  rac{17}{2} \sum_{indexuu=1}^{\infty} \left(  rac{1}{15} ight)^{indexuu} \sum_{indexvv=1}^{\infty}
\left(  rac{2}{5} ight)^{indexvv} \sum_{indexww=1}^{\infty} \left(  rac{2}{3} ight)^{indexww} \&=  rac{17}{2}  rac{1/15}{1-1/15}  rac{2/5}{1-2/5}  rac{2/3}{1-2/3} \&=  rac{17}{21}.
\end{align*}
